MP depletion
What exactly is being referred to in the metaphor of MP depletion?

Example
　When you're working on a project with no finish line in sight, something gets lost, and you lose the energy to move forward.
　Tasks that take a long time to accomplish are unbearable without MP.
 　　Is the MP metaphor appropriate?
 When MP is reduced, the antenna that gathers information from the surroundings stops working.
